---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { getResolvedPath } from "@/utils/all.js";
import projectFourImg from "@/assets/project_4.jpg";
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
import Hero from "@/components/hero.astro";
---

<Layout title="Kalisindh Bhawanimandi Transmission Line">
  <Hero 
    title="Kalisindh Bhawanimandi Transmission Line"
    subtitle="Project Detail"
    image={projectFourImg.src}
    class="mb-6"
  />
  <Container>
      <div class="mt-4">
        <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="list-none flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
            <li><a href={getResolvedPath("/")} class="hover:text-blue-700">Home</a></li>
            <li>/</li>
            <li><a href={getResolvedPath("/projects")} class="hover:text-blue-700">Projects</a></li>
            <li>/</li>
            <li class="text-gray-700 font-semibold">Kalisindh Bhawanimandi Transmission Line</li>
        </ol>
        </nav>
        <div>
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-10">
        <div class="flex-1 order-2 md:order-1">
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Kalisindh Bhawanimandi Transmission Line</h1>
          <div class="text-blue-700 font-medium text-base flex items-center gap-1 mb-1">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="inline w-5 h-5 mr-1 text-blue-600" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17.657 16.657L13.414 20.9a2 2 0 01-2.828 0l-4.243-4.243a8 8 0 1111.314 0z" /><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 11a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" /></svg>
            Kalisindh to Bhawanimandi, Rajasthan
          </div>
          <div class="text-green-700 font-medium text-base flex items-center gap-1 mb-6">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="inline w-5 h-5 mr-1 text-green-600" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 1.343-3 3s1.343 3 3 3 3-1.343 3-3-1.343-3-3-3zm0 13c-4.418 0-8-3.582-8-8 0-3.314 2.686-6 6-6s6 2.686 6 6c0 4.418-3.582 8-8 8z" /></svg>
            â‚¹6.55 Crore
          </div>
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 space-y-5">
            <p>
              The construction of the 220 kV Single Circuit (S/C) Kalisindh Bhawanimandi transmission line, spanning a distance of 35.0 kilometers, was a significant infrastructure project in the power sector, with an estimated budget of INR 6.55 Crore. This project aimed to enhance the electricity transmission capacity and reliability in the region, ultimately benefiting the residents and industries.
            </p>
            <p>
              The scope of work for this project included the installation of high-voltage transmission towers, conductors, insulators, and associated electrical equipment. Skilled engineers and laborers worked diligently to ensure that the transmission line was constructed to the highest safety and quality standards. One of the key objectives of this project was to reduce transmission losses and voltage drops, thereby improving the overall efficiency of electricity distribution. Additionally, it aimed to strengthen the power grid's resilience to adverse weather conditions and load fluctuations, reducing the risk of blackouts.
            </p>
            <p>
              The successful completion of the 220 kV S/C Kalisindh Bhawanimandi transmission line was a crucial milestone in enhancing the region's power infrastructure. It contributed to reliable electricity supply, supported economic growth, and met the increasing energy demands of the area. This investment in the power sector played a pivotal role in fostering development and prosperity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 order-1 md:order-2 flex justify-center">
          <img src={projectFourImg.src} alt="Kalisindh Bhawanimandi Transmission Line" class="rounded-lg shadow w-full max-w-md object-cover" />
        </div>
      </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
